	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102976779470752><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=1&mid=102976779470752>RE: Help settle argument</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=1&mid=102976779470752#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=64677><span id=Sage>xaanru</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>1297 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Aug 19th 10:48 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.40]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Your husband is correct. Wurmslayer is the worst possible 1hs for a warrior who is tanking. I can keep aggro better with a pair of velium daggers than I can with wurmy. My warrior (without haste item) was taunting mobs off of a warrior 2 levels higher (and who had an fbss), who was using wurmslayer, using a large dragonbone shard, and centi shortsword. Sure his hits looked nice, but I actually outdamaged him over the battle, because I was hitting more often, and was at 190+ strength with shaman buffs (he had the shammy buffs too). I logged the battle and totalled up the hits. I outdamaged him nearly every time, and taunted the mob off of him unless he hit a couple crits early (even though he was pulling). If I had the cash for a lammy, he'd have lost aggro, even with the crits.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
